Program 1:To print the given pattern using a for loop in Java:
1. Create a Java class:

    public class PrintPattern {
        public static void main(String[] args) {
            // Loop to print the pattern
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
                System.out.println("*");
            }
        }
    }

2. Compile the Java code:
Save the code as PrintPattern.java and compile it using a Java compiler (e.g., javac PrintPattern.java).

3. Run the compiled code:
Execute the compiled class (e.g., java PrintPattern).

This will produce the desired output:
Code

*
*
*
*
